(Corrects to say developing countries in first paragraph.)  More international savings need to
flow to developing countries and emerging markets, Caijing cited
People’s Bank of  China ’s governor  Zhou Xiaochuan  in a
publication from the Boao forum.  Global savings imbalances will remain for awhile into the
future, the report cited Zhou as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
